From: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Wed, 27 May 2026 07:55:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/damon/sysfs: kobject_del() target dirs

Fixes: c951cd3b8901 ("mm/damon: implement a minimal stub for sysfs-based DAMON interface")
Cc: <stable@vger.kernel.org> # 5.18.x
Signed-off-by: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 mm/damon/sysfs.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/mm/damon/sysfs.c b/mm/damon/sysfs.c
index ea900fb80a800..dcb305ee01acf 100644
--- a/mm/damon/sysfs.c
+++ b/mm/damon/sysfs.c
@@ -335,6 +335,7 @@ static void damon_sysfs_targets_rm_dirs(struct damon_sysfs_targets *targets)
 
 	for (i = 0; i < targets->nr; i++) {
 		damon_sysfs_target_rm_dirs(targets_arr[i]);
+		kobject_del(&targets_arr[i]->kobj);
 		kobject_put(&targets_arr[i]->kobj);
 	}
 	targets->nr = 0;
-- 
2.47.3

